						               													<description>Unofficial expansion of Settlers of Catan.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A set of 32 unique &amp;quot;Pioneers&amp;quot; cards that affect game play from the start of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player is given three random &amp;quot;Pioneers&amp;quot; cards before the game begins and chooses one to keep.  The effects of the chosen card lasts throughout the entire game for the particular player who chose the card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Pioneers card that a player chooses can be a two edged-sword; the card can be anything from &amp;quot;The Sailors&amp;quot; where the player is only able to build ships, but victory is now 2 victory points less than the game's usual number of victory points, to being able to control your opponents for a cost; &amp;quot;The Beggars&amp;quot; gets to extort a resource of their choice from any player who wishes to build a settlement or city. If the builder refuses (or can't) pay the owner of &amp;quot;The Beggars&amp;quot; card, the builder cannot build the settlement or city.  In exchange for this power, &amp;quot;The Beggars&amp;quot; victory is now 1 point more than usual.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Belongs to the Catan Series.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Die Pioniere: http://www.poeppelkiste.de/catan/pioniere/pioniere.htm&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
